  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Also known as retrobulbar hematoma\nMost often due to\nblunt orbital trauma\nCan also be secondary to spontaneous bleeding\n[1]\nCan cause loss of vision within 60-120 min due to abrupt increase in intraocular pressure â†’ orbital compartment syndrome (OCS)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "blunt orbital trauma",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Blunt_orbital_trauma"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Eye pain\nProptosis\nDecreased visual acuity\nElevated\nIOP\n(Do not perform tonometry if globe rupture is suspected)",
